{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κλῆρος</b> <br /> <br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1>, <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>κλᾶρος</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus (see. below), “Leg.Gort.” 5.27, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], ου, ὁ:— <b>lot</b>, κλῆρον ἐσημήναντο ἕκαστος, ἐν δ᾽ ἔβαλον κυνέῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 7.175; κλήρους ἐν κυνέῃ χαλκήρεϊ πάλλον 3.316, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.206; ἐκ κλῆρος ὄρουσεν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 3.325; ἐκ δ᾽ ἔθορε κλῆρος κυνέης 7.182; ἐν δὲ κλήρους ἐβάλοντο 23.352; ἐπὶ κλήρους ἐβάλοντο 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.209, compare “SIG” 1023.94 (from Cos)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κλήρῳ πεπαλάσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.331; κλήρῳ λάχον ἐνθάδ᾽ ἕπεσθαι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.400, compare 23.862, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 187, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.83, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πάντας ἀνέφεδρος ἐπαγκρατίασε τοὺς κ., i.e. he never drew a bye, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1073.29 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; κλήρου κατὰ μοῖραν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Rhesus” 545 (Lyric poetry); διὰ τὴν τοῦ κ. τύχην 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 619d, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κλάροισι θεοπροπέων divining <b>by lots</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.190: hence, of oracles, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 1057, “Ph.” 838; Ἑρμῆς γὰρ ὢν κλήρῳ ποιήσεις οἶδ᾽ ὅτι 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 365; κ. Ἑρμοῦ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 39. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.2</b></Level3> <b>casting of lots, drawing of lots</b>, κ. τίθεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “IA” 1198, compare “Tr.” 186 (Lyric poetry); δοκεῖ δί